hat makes life worth living. And, as Gill shows, this view had a huge impact on the development of natural religion, moral sense theory, aesthetics, and environmentalism.Combining captivating historical details and flashes of humor, A Philosophy of Beauty not only rediscovers and illuminates a fascinating philosopher but also offers an inspiring reflection about the role beauty can play in our lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAestheticsxPhilosophy. 0aAesthetics, Moderny18th century. 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophy of nature. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh  aAdmiration.  aAesthetic Theory.  aAesthetics.  aAffection.  aArt for art's sake.  aAtheism.  aAuthor.  aBelief in God.  aConformity.  aContingency (philosophy).  aCriticism.  aDeclaration of love.  aDeity.  aDeontological ethics.  aDivine providence.  aEfficacy.  aEloquence.  aEmotion.  aEnthusiasm.  aEssay.  aEthics.  aExplanation.  aExtrapolation.  aFeeling.  aFine art.  aFormal garden.  aGod.  aGood and evil.  aGreatness.  aHistory painting.  aHolism.  aHuman.  aHumility.  aIndividual.  aIndulgence.  aInstrumental value.  aIntention.  aLightness.  aLoyalty.  aMoral agency.  aMoral character.  aMorality.  aOn Liberty.  aOriginality.  aPainting.  aPersuasion.  aPhenomenon.  aPhilosophy.  aPiety.  aPoliteness.  aRationality.  aReason.  aReligion.  aReputation.  aResult.  aRighteousness.  aSelf-esteem.  aSelfishness.  aSincerity.  aSoliloquy.  aStoicism.  aSublime (philosophy).  aSympathy.  aTheism.  aThought.  aTranquillity.  aTreatise.  aUniqueness.  aWorship.  aWriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe